Subject: RE: [T2] Greetings and my first question...or two.

Hogan Whittall wrote:
> Anyway, the problem I'm having that's bugging me the most is a
> stumble/misfire at part throttle under load.  It can be somewhat
> intermittent, but is there 90% of the time.  The engine revs fine in
> neutral and most of the time the problem will go away under full
> throttle, but not always.  Feels like a hard miss, it'll start
> bucking about mid throttle and midway through the RPM range.  The two
> things that come to mind are bad fuel since it did sit for at least a
> year or the air flow meter.  I did some searching through the
> archives but didn't come across anything that really addressed the
> problem I'm having, so hopefully someone out there can give me some
> direction.  I've gone through about one tank of fuel since picking it
> up and it does run a LOT better now in general, but this bucking miss
> has got to stop.            

It does kinda sound like an AFM problem. You should inspect it (if you
haven't already) for worn tracks on the board. I had the same problem on my
'78. When I checked it out, the tracks were obviously worn down to nothing
and replacing the AFM fixed 'er right up.


